SOCCER 10 POOL OF THE DAYThursday 24 February S6 V3 Leicester City should add to last week’s 4-1 home win over Randers with away success in tonight’s second leg in Denmark and progress in the Uefa Conference League. More details at www.soccer6.co.za. M1 Bodo/Glimt vs Glasgow Celtic: The Norwegian champions upset Celtic 3-1 away in Glashow last Thursday to take a handy lead home for the second leg of this UEFA Conference League tie.M2 Dinamo Zagreb vs Sevilla: Last season’s Europa League quarter-finalists Dinamo Zagreb must not only end a long losing run against Spanish opposition but also overturn a two-goal deficit to reach the round of 16 as they host competition specialists Sevilla in the second leg of the knockout round play-offs.M3 Lazio vs FC Porto: Porto came from behind to win 2-1 at home last week but it is a slender lead they take to the second leg in Rome.M4 Maccabi Tel Aviv vs PSV Eindhoven: The Dutch club were narrow 1-0 home winners of the first leg of this UEFA Conference League last-16 tie.M5 Olympiakos vs Atalanta: Greek champions Olympiakos will fancy their chances of overturning the aggregate score-line after a narrow 2-1 loss in Italy last Thursday.M6 Partizan Belgrade vs Sparta Prague: Partizan scored 12 minutes from time away in the Czech Republic to win the first leg and give themselves an overwhelming chance to progress in the Conference League.M7 FK Qarabag vs Olympique de Marseille: The first leg at the Stade Vélodrome – Marseille’s maiden fixture against a team from Azerbaijan – resulted in a second successive European win for the French side and back-to-back continental defeats for Qarabağ.M8 Randers vs Leicester City: Comprehensive 4-1 winners of the first leg in England, Leicester take on Randers in northern Denmark with their sights firmly set on a place in the Europa Conference League round of 16.M9 Real Sociedad vs RB Leipzig: Sociedad twice had the lead in Germany last week and eventually came away with a 2-2 draw in the first leg of this Europa League last-16 tie.M10 Arsenal vs Wolverhampton Wanderers: Wolves are only two points behind the Gunners as both clubs battle for a place in next season’s European club competition. Arsenal lost last season at home to Wolves. Suggested permutation:R32.00 1,2 x 3 x 1 x 2,3 x 2,3 x 1 x 2,3 x 3 x 1 x 1